        <updateDate>2017-04-03T15:51:41Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Stop Mass Killings By Violent Terrorists Act</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to&nbsp;prohibit a federally licensed firearms dealer, importer, or manufacturer from transferring, to a person who is a non-licensee, a large capacity ammunition feeding device, unless: (1)&nbsp;the licensee has conducted a criminal background check of the person, and (2)&nbsp;the Department of Justice (DOJ) has verified the truthfulness of certain written responses given by the person with respect to recent contacts by federal law enforcement authorities.</p> <p>In addition, the bill prohibits a federally licensed firearms dealer, importer, or manufacturer from transferring, to a person who is a non-licensee, a semiautomatic weapon (for which a criminal background check is already required under current law), unless DOJ has verified the truthfulness of the person's written responses with respect to recent contacts by federal law enforcement authorities.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
